2026 Regular Session
HOUSE RESOLUTION NO. 179
BY REPRESENTATIVE MARCELLE
DISTRICTS/CRIME PREVENT: Requests the House Committee on Municipal, Parochial
and Cultural Affairs, or a subcommittee thereof, to study the effectiveness of
neighborhood crime prevention and security districts in reducing crime
1 A RESOLUTION
2 To urge and request the House Committee on Municipal, Parochial and Cultural Affairs, or
3 a subcommittee thereof, to study the effectiveness of neighborhood crime prevention
4 and security districts in reducing crime and to report its findings to the House of
5 Representatives of the Legislature of Louisiana no later than March 1, 2027.
6 WHEREAS, neighborhood crime prevention and security districts are created by the
7 Louisiana Legislature pursuant to Chapter 29 of Title 33 of the Louisiana Revised Statutes
8 of 1950 to provide specialized geographic zones to address local safety concerns; and
9 WHEREAS, the creation of a neighborhood crime prevention and security district
10 typically involves establishing a governing body consisting of local government officials,
11 property owners, or appointed community residents who are responsible for overseeing
12 district operations; and
13 WHEREAS, these governing bodies are often tasked with creating policies,
14 developing budgets, and overseeing security initiatives; and
15 WHEREAS, the powers of the districts typically include the ability to deploy
16 enhanced patrols and security measures, which allow the districts to increase law
17 enforcement visibility; and
18 WHEREAS, the districts may also utilize surveillance and technology deployment,
19 such as installing security cameras, lighting, or other crime prevention tools; and
