1 WHEREAS, the districts are typically funded through a parcel fee levied by or on
2 behalf of the district, subject to the approval of the residents of the respective districts; and
3 WHEREAS, the majority of the neighborhood crime prevention and security districts
4 in the state are located within the parishes of Orleans and East Baton Rouge; and
5 WHEREAS, there is a need for a comprehensive study on whether these parishes
6 have experienced a reduction in crime as a result of the creation of neighborhood crime
7 prevention and security districts within their localities; and
8 WHEREAS, there is also a need for an examination of whether the funds generated
9 from the parcel fees levied by or on behalf of the districts are being used efficiently and
10 whether the uses of such funds align with the goals and objectives of the districts.
11 THEREFORE, BE IT RESOLVED that the House of Representatives of the
12 Legislature of Louisiana does hereby urge and request the House Committee on Municipal,
13 Parochial and Cultural Affairs, or a subcommittee thereof, to study the effectiveness of
14 neighborhood crime prevention and security districts in reducing crime and to report its
15 findings to the House of Representatives of the Legislature of Louisiana no later than
16 March 1, 2027.
